obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (20800)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title and extent.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00027_194809_1517807324417&sectionId=20800&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00027_194809_1517807324417
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Dock Workers (Regulation of`
  line `Employment) Act, 1948.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India ^1[except the State of Jammu and Kashmir*].`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 3 of 1951, s. 3 and the Schedule, for "except part B States".`
  line `*. *Vide* Notification No. S.O. 3912 (E), dated 30th October, 2019, this Act is made applicable to the Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir and the Union territory of Ladakh.`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (20801)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00027_194809_1517807324417&sectionId=20801&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00027_194809_1517807324417
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless there is anything repugnant in the subject or context, --`
  line
  line `^1[(a) "Board" means a Dock Labour Board established under section 5A;]`
  line
  line `^2[(aa) "cargo" includes anything carried or to be carried in a ship or other vessel;]`
  line
  line `(b) "dock worker" means a person employed or to be employed in, or in the vicinity of, any port`
  line `on work in connection with the loading, unloading, movement or storage of cargoes, or work in`
  line `connection with the preparation of ships or other vessels for the receipt or discharge of cargoes or`
  line `leaving port;`
  line
  line `(c) "employer", in relation to a dock worker, means the person by whom he is employed or to be`
  line `employed as aforesaid;`
  line
  line `(d) "Government" means, in relation to any major port, the Central Government and, in relation`
  line `to any other port, the State Government;`
  line
  line `(e) "scheme" means a scheme made under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 8 of 1962, s. 2 (w.e.f. 1-6-1962).`
  line
  line `2. Clause (a) re-lettered as clause (aa) by s. 2, ibid, (w.e.f. 1-6-1962).`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (20802)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Scheme for ensuring regular employment of workers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00027_194809_1517807324417&sectionId=20802&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00027_194809_1517807324417
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) Provision may be made by a`
  line `scheme for the registration of dock workers ^1[and employers] with a view to ensuring greater regularity`
  line `of employment and for regulating the employment of dock workers, whether registered or not, in a port.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, a scheme may provide--`
  line
  line `(a) for the application of the scheme to such classes of dock workers and employers as may be`
  line `specified therein;`
  line
  line `(b) for defining the obligations of dock workers and employers subject to the fulfilment of which`
  line `the scheme may apply to them and the circumstances in which the scheme shall cease to apply to any`
  line `dock workers or employers;`
  line
  line `(c) for regulating the recruitment and entry into the scheme of dock workers, ^2[and the`
  line `registration of dock workers and employers], including the maintenance of registers, the removal`
  line `either temporarily or permanently, of names from the registers and the imposition of fees for`
  line registration;
  line
  line `(d) for regulating the employment of dock workers, whether registered or not, and the terms and`
  line `conditions of such employment, including rates of remuneration, hours of work and conditions as to`
  line `holidays and pay in respect thereof;`
  line
  line `(e) for securing that, in respect of periods during which employment, or full employment, is not`
  line `available for dock workers to whom the scheme applies and who are available for work, such workers`
  line `will, subject to the conditions of the scheme, receive a minimum pay;`
  line
  line `(f) for prohibiting, restricting or otherwise controlling the employment of dock workers to whom`
  line `the scheme does not apply and the employment of dock workers by employers to whom the scheme`
  line `does not apply;`
  line
  line `^3[(ff) for creating such fund or funds as may be necessary or expedient for the purposes of the`
  line `scheme and for the administration of such fund or funds;]`
  line
  line `(g) for the training ^4*** of dock workers, in so far as satisfactory provision therefore does not`
  line `exist apart from the scheme;`
  line
  line `^5[(gg) for the welfare of the officers and other staff of the Board;]`
  line
  line `^6* * * * * *`
  line
  line `(i) for the manner in which, and the persons by whom, the cost of operating the scheme is to be`
  line defrayed;
  line
  line `^7(j) for constituting ^8*** the authority to be responsible for the administration of the scheme;]`
  line
  line `(k) for such incidental and supplementary matters as may necessary or expedient for the purposes`
  line `of the scheme.`
  line
  line `(3) A scheme may further provide that a contravention of any provision thereof shall be punishable`
  line `with imprisonment for such term as may be specified but in no case exceeding three months in respect of`
  line `a first contravention or six months in respect of any subsequent contravention, or with fine which may`
  line `extend to such amount as may be specified but in no case exceeding five hundred rupees in respect of a`
  line `first contravention or one thousand rupees in respect of any subsequent contravention, or with both`
  line `imprisonment and fine as aforesaid.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by s. 3, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-6-1962).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for "and their registration" (w.e.f. 1-6-1962).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 8 of 1962, s. 3 (w.e.f. 1-6-1962).`
  line
  line `4. The words "and welfare" omitted by Act 54 of 1986, s. 23 (w.e.f. 15-4-1987).`
  line
  line `5. Ins. by Act 31 of 1970, s. 2`
  line
  line `6 Omitted by Act 54 of 1986, s. 23 (w.e.f. 15-4-1987).`
  line
  line `7 Subs. by Act 29 of 1949, s. 2, for clause (j).`
  line
  line `8 The words "whether as a body corporate or otherwise" omitted by Act 8 of 1962, s. 3 (w.e.f. 1-6-1962).`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (20803)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Making, variation and revocation of schemes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00027_194809_1517807324417&sectionId=20803&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00027_194809_1517807324417
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette and subject to the condition of previous publication, make one or more schemes for a`
  line `port or group of ports, and may in the like manner and subject to the like condition add to, amend, vary or`
  line `revoke any scheme made by it.`
  line
  line `(2) The provisions of section 23 of the General Clauses Act, 1897 (10 of 1897), shall apply to the`
  line `exercise of a power given by sub-section (1) as they apply to the exercise of a power given by a Central`
  line `Act to make rules subject to the condition of previous publication.`
  line
  line `(3) The Government may direct the port authority of any port to prepare, in accordance with such`
  line `instructions as may from time to time be given to it, one or more draft schemes for the port, and the port`
  line `authority shall comply with such direction.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (20804)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Advisory Committees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00027_194809_1517807324417&sectionId=20804&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00027_194809_1517807324417
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Government may, or if it decides to make any scheme under`
  line `section 4, shall, constitute an Advisory Committee, to advise upon such matters arising out of the`
  line `administration of this Act or any scheme made thereunder as the Government may refer to it for advice.`
  line
  line `^1[(2) The members of the Advisory Committee shall be appointed by the Government and shall be of`
  line `such number and chosen in such manner as may be prescribed by rules made under this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Advisory Committee shall include an equal number of members representing--`
  line
  line `(i) the Government,`
  line
  line `(ii) the dock workers, and`
  line
  line `(iii) the employers of dock workers, and shipping companies.]`
  line
  line `(3) The Chairman of the Advisory Committee shall be one of the members appointed to represent the`
  line `Government, nominated in this behalf by the Government.`
  line
  line `(4) The Government shall publish in the Official Gazette the names of all members of the Advisory`
  line Committee.
  line
  line `^2* * * * * *`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 8 of 1962, s. 4, for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 1-6-1962).`
  line
  line `2. Omitted by s. 4, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-6-1962).`
obj_root_law_sections_5_a:
  sectionId (20805)
  sectionNo 5A
  orderNo 6
  title `Dock Labour Boards.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 5, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-6-1962).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00027_194809_1517807324417&sectionId=20805&sectionno=5A&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00027_194809_1517807324417
obj_root_law_sections_5_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[5A. Dock Labour Boards.--(1) The Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `establish a Dock Labour Board for a port or group of ports to be known by such name as may be specified`
  line `in the notification.`
  line
  line `(2) Every such Board shall be a body corporate with the name aforesaid, having perpetual succession`
  line `and a common seal with power to acquire, hold and dispose of property and to contract and may, by that`
  line `name, sue and be sued.`
  line
  line `(3) Every such Board shall consist of a Chairman and such number of other members as may he`
  line `appointed by the Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that every such Board shall include an equal number of members representing--`
  line
  line `(i) the Government,`
  line
  line `(ii) the dock workers, and`
  line
  line `(iii) the employers of dock workers, and shipping companies.`
  line
  line `(4) The Chairman of a Board shall be one of the members appointed to represent the Government,`
  line `and nominated in this behalf by the Government.]`
obj_root_law_sections_5_b:
  sectionId (20806)
  sectionNo 5B
  orderNo 7
  title `Functions of a Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 5, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-6-1962).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00027_194809_1517807324417&sectionId=20806&sectionno=5B&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00027_194809_1517807324417
obj_root_law_sections_5_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[5B. Functions of a Board.--(1) A Board shall be responsible for administering the scheme for the`
  line `port or group of ports for which it has been established and shall exercise such powers and perform such`
  line `functions as may be conferred on it by the scheme.`
  line
  line `(2) In the exercise of its powers and the discharge of its functions, a Board shall be bound by such`
  line `directions as the Government may, for reasons to be stated in writing, give to it from time to time.]`
obj_root_law_sections_5_c:
  sectionId (20807)
  sectionNo 5C
  orderNo 8
  title `Accounts and audit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_c_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 5, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-6-1962).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00027_194809_1517807324417&sectionId=20807&sectionno=5C&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00027_194809_1517807324417
obj_root_law_sections_5_c_content:
  string
  line `^1[5C. Accounts and audit.--(1) Every Board shall maintain proper accounts and other relevant`
  line `records and prepare an annual statement of accounts, including a balance-sheet in such form as may be`
  line `prescribed by rules made under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The accounts of the Board shall be audited annually by the Comptroller and Auditor-General of`
  line `India or by such other auditors qualified to act as auditors of companies under the law for the time being`
  line `in force relating to companies, as the Government may appoint.`
  line
  line `(3) The auditors shall, at all reasonable times, have access to the books of accounts and other`
  line `documents of the Board and may, for the purposes of the audit, call for such explanation and information`
  line `as they may require or examine any member or officer of the Board.`
  line
  line `(4) The auditors shall forward to the Government a copy of their report together with an audited copy`
  line `of the accounts of the Board.`
  line
  line `(5) The cost of the audit as determined by the Government shall be paid GUI of the funds of the`
  line Board.]
obj_root_law_sections_5_d:
  sectionId (20808)
  sectionNo 5D
  orderNo 9
  title `Annual report.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_d_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 56 of 1988, s. 2.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00027_194809_1517807324417&sectionId=20808&sectionno=5D&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00027_194809_1517807324417
obj_root_law_sections_5_d_content:
  string
  line `^1[5D. Annual report.--Every Board shall prepare, in such form and at such time in each financial`
  line `year as may be specified by rules made under this Act, its annual report, giving full accounts of its`
  line `activities during the previous financial year, and submit a copy thereof to the Government.]`
obj_root_law_sections_5_e:
  sectionId (20809)
  sectionNo 5E
  orderNo 10
  title `Annual report and audited accounts, to be laid before Parliament or Legislature.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_e_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 56 of 1988, s. 2.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00027_194809_1517807324417&sectionId=20809&sectionno=5E&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00027_194809_1517807324417
obj_root_law_sections_5_e_content:
  string
  line `^1[5E. Annual report and audited accounts, to be laid before Parliament or Legislature.--The`
  line `annual report, and the audited accounts of the Board, together with auditor's report thereon and a review`
  line `by the Government on the working of the Board, shall, within a period of nine months of the close of the`
  line `financial year, be laid before each House of Parliament, if such report and accounts have been submitted`
  line `to the Central Government, and before the Legislature of the State, if such report and accounts have been`
  line `submitted to the State Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that where such report, accounts and the review are not laid before Parliament or, as the`
  line `case may be, before the Legislature of the State within the said period, the same shall be so laid thereafter`
  line `along with the reasons for the delay.]`
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (20810)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 11
  title Inspectors.
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00027_194809_1517807324417&sectionId=20810&sectionno=6&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00027_194809_1517807324417
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, appoint such`
  line `persons as it thinks fit to be Inspectors for the purposes of this Act at such ports as may be specified in the`
  line notification.
  line
  line `(2) Every Inspector shall be deemed to be a public servant within the meaning of the Indian Penal`
  line `Code (45 of 1860).`
  line
  line `(3) An Inspector may, at any port for which he is appointed,--`
  line
  line `(a) enter, with such assistance (if any) as he thinks fit, any premises or vessel where dock workers`
  line `are employed;`
  line
  line `(b) require any authority or person to produce any register, muster-roll or other document relating`
  line `to the employment of dock workers, and examine such document;`
  line
  line `(c) take on the spot or otherwise the evidence of any person for the purpose of ascertaining`
  line `whether the provisions of any scheme made for the port are, or have been, complied with.`
  line
  line `(4) The Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, prescribed the manner in which and`
  line `the persons by whom complaints regarding contravention of any provision of a scheme may be made to`
  line `an Inspector and the duties of the Inspector in relation to such complaints.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6_a:
  sectionId (20811)
  sectionNo 6A
  orderNo 12
  title `Power to order inquiry.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 8 of 1962, s. 6 (w.e.f. 1-6-1962).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00027_194809_1517807324417&sectionId=20811&sectionno=6A&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00027_194809_1517807324417
obj_root_law_sections_6_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[6A. Power to order inquiry.--(1) The Government may, at any time, appoint any person to`
  line `investigate or inquire into the working of a Board and submit a report to the Government.`
  line
  line `(2) The Board shall give to the person so appointed all facilities for the proper conduct of the`
  line `investigation or inquiry and furnish to him such documents, accounts or information in the possession of`
  line `the Board as he may require.]`
obj_root_law_sections_6_b:
  sectionId (20812)
  sectionNo 6B
  orderNo 13
  title `Power to supersede a Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 8 of 1962, s. 6 (w.e.f. 1-6-1962).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00027_194809_1517807324417&sectionId=20812&sectionno=6B&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00027_194809_1517807324417
obj_root_law_sections_6_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[6B. Power to supersede a Board.--(1) If, on consideration of the report under section 6A or`
  line `otherwise, the Government is of opinion--`
  line
  line `(a) that, on account of a grave emergency, a Board is unable to perform its functions, or`
  line
  line `(b) that a Board has persistently made default in the discharge of its functions or has exceeded or`
  line `abused its powers,`
  line
  line `the Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, supersede the Board for such period as may`
  line `be specified in the notification:`
  line
  line `Provided that, before issuing a notification under this sub-section on any of the grounds mentioned in`
  line `clause (b), the Government shall give a reasonable opportunity to the Board to show cause why it should`
  line `not be superseded and shall consider the explanations and objections, if any, of the Board.`
  line
  line `(2) Upon the publication of a notification under sub-section (1),--`
  line
  line `(a) all the members of the Board shall, as from the date of such publication, vacate their offices as`
  line `such members;`
  line
  line `(b) all the powers and functions which may be exercised or performed by the Board shall, during`
  line `the period of supersession, be exercised or performed by such person as may be specified in the`
  line notification;
  line
  line `(c) all funds and other property vested in the Board shall, during the period of supersession, vest`
  line `in the Government.`
  line
  line `(3) On the expiration of the period of supersession specified in the notification issued under`
  line `sub-section (1), the Government may--`
  line
  line `(a) extend the period of supersession for such further period as it may consider necessary; or`
  line
  line `(b) re-establish the Board in the manner provided in section 5A.]`
obj_root_law_sections_6_c:
  sectionId (20813)
  sectionNo 6C
  orderNo 14
  title `Acts or proceeding of Board and Advisory Committee not to be invalidated.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_c_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 8 of 1962, s. 6 (w.e.f. 1-6-1962).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00027_194809_1517807324417&sectionId=20813&sectionno=6C&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00027_194809_1517807324417
obj_root_law_sections_6_c_content:
  string
  line `^1[6C. Acts or proceeding of Board and Advisory Committee not to be invalidated.--No act or`
  line `proceeding of a Board or the Advisory Committee shall be invalid merely by reason of--`
  line
  line `(a) any vacancy in, or any defect in the constitution of, the Board or the Advisory Committee, or`
  line
  line `(b) any defect in the appointment of a person acting as a member of the Board or the Advisory`
  line `Committee, or`
  line
  line `(c) any irregularity in the procedure of the Board or the Advisory Committee not affecting the`
  line `merits of the case.]`
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (20814)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 15
  title `Cognizance of offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes `1. See now the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00027_194809_1517807324417&sectionId=20814&sectionno=7&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00027_194809_1517807324417
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) No Court shall take cognizance of any offence made punishable by`
  line `a scheme or of any abetment thereof, except on a report in writing of the facts constituting such offence or`
  line `abetment made by an Inspector or by a person specially authorised in this behalf by the Government.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of Criminal Procedure 1898^1`
  line `(5 of 1898), an`
  line `offence made punishable by a scheme or an abetment thereof shall be triable only by a Presidency`
  line `Magistrate or a Magistrate of the first class.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_a:
  sectionId (20815)
  sectionNo 7A
  orderNo 16
  title `Offences by companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 31 of 1970, s. 3.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00027_194809_1517807324417&sectionId=20815&sectionno=7A&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00027_194809_1517807324417
obj_root_law_sections_7_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[7A. Offences by companies.--(1) If the person committing an offence made punishable by a`
  line `scheme or any abetment thereof is a company, every person who, at the time the offence or abetment was`
  line `committed, was in charge of, and was responsible to, the company for the conduct of the business of the`
  line `company, as well as the company, shall be deemed to be guilty of the offence or abetment and shall be`
  line `liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall render any such person liable to any`
  line `punishment, if he proves that the offence or abetment was committed without his knowledge or that he`
  line `exercised all due diligence to prevent the commission of such offence or abetment.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), where an offence made punishable by a`
  line `scheme or any abetment thereof has been committed by a company and it is proved that the offence or`
  line `abetment has been committed with the consent or connivance of, or is attributable to any neglect on the`
  line `part of, any director, manager, secretary or other officer of the company, such director, manager, secretary`
  line `or other officer shall also be deemed to be guilty of that offence or abetment and shall be liable to be`
  line `proceeded against and punished accordingly.`
  line
  line `Explanation. -- For the purposes of this section,--`
  line
  line `(a) "company" means any body corporate and includes a firm and other association of`
  line `individuals; and`
  line
  line `(b) "director", in relation to a firm, means a partner in the firm.]`
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (20816)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 17
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00027_194809_1517807324417&sectionId=20816&sectionno=8&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00027_194809_1517807324417
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `^1[8. Power to make rules.--(1) The Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, make`
  line `rules to give effect to the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the forgoing power, such rules may provide`
  line for--
  line
  line `(a) the compositions of the Advisory Committee and Boards and the manner in which members`
  line `of the Advisory Committee and the Boards shall be chosen;`
  line
  line `(b) the term of office of, and the manner of filling casual vacancies among, the members of a`
  line `Board or the Advisory Committee;`
  line
  line `(c) the meetings of a Board and the Advisory Committee, the quorum for such meetings and the`
  line `conduct of business thereat;`
  line
  line `(d) the conditions subject to which, and the mode in which, contracts may be entered into by or`
  line `on behalf of a Board;`
  line
  line `(e) the allowances, if any, payable, to the members of a Board or the Advisory Committee;`
  line
  line `(f) the disqualifications for membership of a Board;`
  line
  line `(g) the form in which a Board shall prepare its annual statement of accounts and the`
  line `balance- sheet.`
  line
  line `^2* * * * * *]`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 8 of 1962, s. 7 (w.e.f. 1-6-1962).`
  line
  line `2. Omitted by Act 49 of 1980, s. 4.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_a:
  sectionId (20817)
  sectionNo 8A
  orderNo 18
  title `Schemes and rules to be laid before Parliament.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00027_194809_1517807324417&sectionId=20817&sectionno=8A&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00027_194809_1517807324417
obj_root_law_sections_8_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[ ^2[8A. Schemes and rules to be laid before Parliament.-- Every scheme and every rule made under`
  line `this Act by the Central Government shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each House of`
  line `Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in one session`
  line `or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately following the`
  line `session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification in the scheme`
  line `or rule or both Houses agree that the scheme or rule should not be made, the scheme or rule shall`
  line `thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that`
  line `any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done`
  line `under that scheme or rule.]]`
obj_root_law_sections_8_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 8 of 1962, s. 7 (w.e.f. 1-6-1962).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by s. 5, ibid.`
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (20818)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 19
  title Saving.
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 8 of 1962, s. 7 (w.e.f. 1-6-1962).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00027_194809_1517807324417&sectionId=20818&sectionno=9&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00027_194809_1517807324417
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `^1[9. Saving.--Every Dock Labour Board established for a port or a group of ports before the`
  line `commencement of the Dock Workers (Regulation of Employment) Amendment Act, 1962 (8 of 1962),`
  line `under a scheme made under section 4, and functioning as such immediately before such commencement`
  line `shall be deemed to be a Board established under section 5A and, accordingly, all the provisions of this`
  line `Act shall apply to every such Board.]`
